  "schemaVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "_comment": "Skill: fetch and deterministically rate all 5 status-report dimensions for one initiative in a single agent tool call, replacing 6-8 sequential Dataverse MCP read_query round-trips. KPI picklist ints are the VERIFIED pdausa mapping (493840001=Red, 493840002=Yellow, 493840003=Green, 493840000=N/A/NotSet) \u2014 confirmed live against pum_statusreportings on 2026-07-03; this differs from older repo docs which had it backwards. Aggregates use FetchXml (aggregate=\"true\") via the List rows action's fetchXml parameter \u2014 this is the first use of this technique in the repo; VERIFY the returned alias key names (e.g. 'incompletecount') match the connector's actual JSON shape on first test run via the flow-debugger loop, and adjust the first()/coalesce() addressing if the connector nests aggregate values differently. Resources/Financials rating simplifications: no total-record N/A detection for Timeline/Quality (documented simplification for the demo \u2014 see plan). Quality uses pum_impact=Negative(493840001) as the proxy signal since pum_lessonslearned has no dedicated Quality category. Cache/mode handling (Check_Cache branch) is added in Phase 2 via update-flow.ps1 once pum_statusdraftcache exists \u2014 this version always computes fresh."
}
